1) 1 legal expert support provided to the Ombudsman's Office on asylum; 
2) Technical support to Border Guards Service of SCNS: 39 information stands handed over,  2 refugee reception rooms at Osh and Manas airports are renovated and fully equipped to enhance efficient and functional referral mechanisms and access to territory. 
3) UNHCR provided 22 capacity building activities for 232 law enforcement officers, border guards personnel, staff of NHRIs (National Human Rights Institutions ), refuge

Within the “Effective HIV and TB Control Project in the Kyrgyz Republic”  UNDP supported a series of activities aimed at creating supportive environment for universal access to HIV and TB related services, which include:
•	Strengthening Health system and communities for Integrated People-centered Services;
•	Creating favorable legal and social conditions for overcoming HIV and TB infection;
•	Ensuring the coordination and sustainability of HIV and TB-related programmes.
